            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <p/>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" resp="#JP">
                <p>In detailed study of the theatre in 1986 this was the only inscription identified on the preserved seats. It is a reasonable assumption that since the same pair of letters is repeated, they have the same reference. The text on the vertical face of the seat (text B) is presented in the form of a monogram, with alpha much smaller and placed within the pi. The implication of the larger letters set out on the horizontal surface (text A) is that the small alpha should be read first in resolving such a monogrammatic presentation.</p>
            </div>
